<section class="faq-section">
<h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

<div class="faq-item">
<div class="faq-q">What is fulfillment in e-commerce?</div>
<div class="faq-a">Fulfillment is the complete process of receiving, storing, picking, packing, and shipping products on behalf of an online store. A fulfillment provider handles all physical logistics so the store owner can focus on marketing, sales, and product development. It typically includes 7 core services: receiving, storage, order picking, packing, shipping, returns management, and reporting.</div>
</div>

<div class="faq-item">
<div class="faq-q">Who needs fulfillment services?</div>
<div class="faq-a">Fulfillment services benefit any online store that ships more than 20-30 orders per day, lacks warehouse space or staff, wants to scale without adding operational complexity, or needs faster delivery times. It is especially valuable for businesses selling on multiple channels (website plus marketplaces) where centralized inventory management becomes critical.</div>
</div>

<div class="faq-item">
<div class="faq-q">What is the difference between fulfillment and warehousing?</div>
<div class="faq-a">Warehousing is just storage, keeping products in a facility. Fulfillment is a complete service that includes warehousing plus order processing, picking, packing, shipping, returns handling, and technology integration. A warehouse stores your goods; a fulfillment center actively processes and ships your orders to customers every day.</div>
</div>
